This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with OCR, which is a common computer vision task. It may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it discusses language models. The use of neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on character recognition and language modeling suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
